  "response_text": "The commercial begins with a red, textured product display unrelated to the classroom scene that follows. A bottle and tall glass of Redd’s Apple Ale stand against a deep red background, with a red apple beside them. Visible text reads “REDD’S APPLE ALE” on the glass and bottle, and “PICK DIFFERENT” to the right.\n\nThe scene then changes to a bright elementary classroom. A clean-cut adult man in a dark suit, white shirt, and striped tie sits at a small table with several young children. The room is colorful and busy, with shelves, bins, art supplies, children’s drawings, and a bulletin board in the background. On the table are sheets of colored paper, small craft pieces, and little bottles of paint or glue. The man sits upright in the middle, looking serious and attentive, while children sit around him as if in a classroom discussion.\n\nTwo children are shown closely: a blonde girl with long wavy hair wearing a denim jumper over a light shirt with small dots, and a boy with short dark hair wearing a blue plaid shirt. Both face toward the adult. The boy raises both hands in front of him, holding up two fingers on each hand, emphasizing “two.” The girl watches with her mouth slightly open, as if reacting or answering along with him. Small bottles in green, blue, and yellow sit on the table in front of them.\n\nAcross the table, two other children are visible: a blond curly-haired boy in a brown hoodie over a striped shirt, and a girl with her hair in a high bun wearing a gray-and-white striped top. They look toward the adult man. The girl with the bun speaks animatedly, her mouth open and her hand lifting slightly from the table, while the boy beside her watches with a more neutral, curious expression.\n\nBack at the center table view, the suited man looks down and listens as the children continue. The classroom setting remains cheerful and art-focused, with bright paper, paint bottles, and craft materials spread around. The adult appears to be leading the conversation, but the children are doing most of the gesturing and reacting.\n\nThe boy in the blue plaid shirt then becomes the focus. Seated beside the blonde girl in the denim jumper, he talks with growing enthusiasm. He sits upright at first, then begins moving his head and shoulders in an exaggerated, playful way. He tilts his head from side to side and rolls it around while also moving one hand near the tabletop. The blonde girl turns toward him, watching closely. The paint bottles remain lined up in the foreground, and behind them are classroom shelves with bins and jars of supplies.\n\nThe boy continues his demonstration more dramatically. He raises one hand beside his head and waves it while moving his head back and forth, as if trying to show he can do more than one thing at once. His face is animated, and his movements become broad and quick. The blonde girl keeps her hands near the table and watches him with a small smile, while an adult hand enters from the right side of the table, suggesting the suited man is nearby and responding.\n\nThe view widens again to include the suited man and more of the group. The boy’s arm swings across the foreground in front of the man and the blonde girl. The man watches him, then lifts one hand, palm forward, as if gently interrupting or stopping the demonstration. The boy continues moving, partly out of view on the right, while the girl in the denim jumper looks between the man and the boy. The blond curly-haired child is visible on the left, also watching.\n\nThe suited man reaches across the table and catches or steadies the boy’s moving hand, holding it in midair to pause the action. His expression remains calm and focused, as if managing the lively moment. The boy smiles broadly at the edge of the frame, and the children around the table continue watching.\n\nThe commercial then cuts to a clean white background. On the left is a black iPhone displaying a grid of colorful app icons. To its right, large orange text reads, “Doing two things at once is better.” Fine gray legal text appears along the bottom, too small to read clearly in full. The final screen shows the blue AT&T globe logo above the black “at&t” wordmark, with the website “att.com/network” below on a plain light background.",
